      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Signal triangulation is technically possible, as varying signal strengths at multiple points can approximate a location, but this requires multiple synchronized receivers, not just a single SSID. A single Wi-Fi signal fluctuation alone is insufficient evidence of active, invasive monitoring from a neighbor. While the name is certainly provocative, interpreting every technical occurrence as malicious surveillance can lead to unnecessary worry about complex, unseen technologies.",
      "source": "target",
